# Migration Command

Through database migration process utilizes `https://github.com/rubenv/sql-migrate`, we don't use its generic command to run it. This is to keep the configuration centralized under .env.

## Commands

We can run the migration by cobra command:

```shell
app migration up
```
To migrate up

and

```shell
app migration down
```
To migrate down

## Implementation

The `migrate` command accesses migration files in the `migration/` directory through the `&FileMigrationSource` object from the `github.com/rubenv/sql-migrate` library. Then it runs the `Exec` function with the `ProvideSqlx` provider from the `internal/di/provider` package.

## Migration File Structure

```
migration/
├── 001_create_users.up.sql
├── 001_create_users.down.sql
├── 002_create_projects.up.sql
└── 002_create_projects.down.sql
```

## Migration Naming Convention

- Format: `{sequence}_{description}.{direction}.sql`
- Example: `001_create_users.up.sql`
- Sequence: 3-digit zero-padded numbers (001, 002, 003...)
- Description: snake_case descriptive name
- Direction: `up` for forward migration, `down` for rollback

## Migration Table

- Default table name: `gorp_migrations`
- Tracks applied migrations and their timestamps
- Automatically created by sql-migrate library

## Environment Support

- Uses centralized configuration from .env
- Database connection via `ProvideSqlx` provider
- Supports different environments (dev/staging/prod) through config